---
// Single "Save to Union" CTA shown only on alive share pages.
// Per Plan C decision 1, the public page never asks for login —
// saving happens IN the app, after install. This block frames the
// install step as "Save to Union" so the user understands the
// value they get from installing.
//
// If Union is installed and AASA-verified, the universal-link tap
// from the original messaging app would already have opened the
// app and skipped this page entirely. By the time the user sees
// this CTA, they're on web without the app installed (or AASA
// hasn't verified yet) — so the actionable next step is install.
//
// The store buttons use the official App Store and Google Play
// badge artwork (committed under public/badges/) — brand guidelines
// require the official lockups rather than custom recreations.
// Apple and Google badges have different intrinsic aspect ratios,
// so they are presented at equal HEIGHT, the standard way to show
// them together.

// App Store numeric ID (6770460200) and Android package
// (app.unionwith) both match union-app's eas.json / app.json.
---

<section class="cta-card">
  <h2>Save this in Union</h2>
  <p class="hint">
    Install Union and tap the link again — your saved prayer lands in your journal alongside the rest.
  </p>
  <div class="store-links">
    <a class="store-badge store-badge--apple" href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id6770460200">
      <img src="/badges/app-store-badge.svg" alt="Download on the App Store" />
    </a>
    <a class="store-badge store-badge--google" href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=app.unionwith">
      <img src="/badges/google-play-badge.png" alt="Get it on Google Play" />
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cta-card {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: 48px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }
  .cta-card h2 {
    font-family: var(--display-font);
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .hint {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 24px 0;
  }
  .store-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .store-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    /* Clear space around each badge per brand guidelines. */
    padding: 4px;
  }
  .store-badge img {
    width: auto;
    display: block;
  }
  /* Per-badge heights, not equal heights: the official badges have
     different proportions (the App Store lockup is squarer, Google
     Play wider + more colour-heavy), so equal pixel height makes
     Google read as larger. Sizing Google a little shorter than the
     App Store badge balances the two into a matched pair. */
  .store-badge--apple img {
    height: 48px;
  }
  .store-badge--google img {
    height: 40px;
  }
</style>
